article.headline: Princeton 68, Brown 61
article.story: PRINCETON, N.J. (AP) -- Judson Wallace scored 20 points as Princeton surged past Brown to post a 68-61 win on Saturday. The victory gave Princeton a stranglehold on the Ivy League race as the Tigers (8-1) took a 1 1/2 game lead over Brown (7-3) with five games to play. Princeton won its fourth straight game to improve to 15-7 overall, while Brown dropped to 11-12. Princeton went on an 8-0 run to jump ahead for good at 56-53 with 5:54 to go. Andre Logan got a putback on a Max Schafer airball and then Will Venable nailed two free throws to tie it. Schafer followed with a 3-pointer from the right corner to put the Tigers on top with 5:54 remaining. Mike Martin topped four Brown players in double figures with 14 points. The Tigers trailed by as many as nine in the first half but cut it to one at 29-28 at the break.
